title: (What's the story) Morning glory
body:
by dailydoseoftrash7

Jungkook pulled Yoongi forward, both of their bodies colliding slightly, and continued to hug him warmly, successfully cutting Yoongi’s sentence with his own.
“Hyung…just listen, okay?”

“Hmmmm…”

“People are going to reject us. Many families might not even see our papers because we are gay and young. But that’s part of the process, right? You heard the officials. That woman who came to check whether our house was fit to accommodate a child even said that our house was far better amongst the ones she had inspected, even one of the best. She said she’ll try to get us on the top of her list.”

Yoongi huffed a laugh from his place on Jungkook’s chest, “But don’t they tell these things to every couple?”

or

Startled, Taehyung woke up and immediately started crying. Jungkook glared at everyone to get quite and Yoongi gently held him, close to his chest, murmuring sweet nothings – my baby, Taehyung-ie, don’t worry, go to sleep, hush…
As if, Yoongi had cast a spell, Taehyung gurgled and went back to sleep.

or

the one where yoongi and jungkook adopt taehyung

body:
As I Told You-Kim Namjoon

Sequel to “As I Told You-Pt.2”

“Will you be my first dance?”
Namjoon smiled softly and nodded once before caressing the back of your hand. A tickling sensation ran down your spine as he enveloped your fingers and guided you into the massive crowd moving merrily with the beautiful tune flying around the ballroom. His dimples never left his cheeks and his grasp, gentle as the summer breeze, controlled your every step with grace.

The prince turned you around and you could devise numerous faces observing the both of you. If he noticed them too, he did not attempt to acknowledge their presence. He made the environment around him go blank for his mere figure got all your attention-”Are you enjoying the ball?”-he asked nicely as he continued twirling your body with incredible ease. His movements were slow yet steady as if your bodies were floating in the softest cloud in earth.  You knew that if your eyes closed voluntarily, you surely would have fallen asleep due to Namjoon’s calming presence.

He made you dream like no ones else did.

He empowered you greatly, motivating every inch of your soul to follow what made you happy. Maybe it was because of his training years to inherit his father’s throne that provided him with such ease with words, such a social intelligence. You did not know the whereabouts yet you marvelled with them gleefully-“Indeed I am”-you replied as he thrust you even further into his embrace and introduced you to the song’s grand finale. The string quartet boomed their ending piece whereas Namjoon threw your torso slightly backwards, vending his body with yours.

The crowd quickly smiled and clapped brightly, illuminating the vast room. However, the prince’s charming eyes captivated your attention, legs quivering because of their intensity-“The evening is a partial success…”

Your eyebrows quirked downwards, confusion settling on your face-“Aren’t you enjoying-”

But he decided to interrupt you by gathering your chin with two fingers and propping your head upwards. Another melody erupted from the four instruments, the violin singing outstandingly. You fluttered your eyes close in order to enjoy the melody yet Namjoon had other plans in mind, vending slightly downwards and mumbling on your lips-“I will be even happier after this”

And without more explanation, he landed his soft lips on your glossy ones. People gasped, others cheered but you surely knew that the music halted abruptly; leaving your drumming heart without company. His limbs embraced you completely, tickling the small of your back like light feathers. When he pulled back you had to bite on your lower lip to contain the widening grin spreading on your lips-“Would you stay with me, Y/N?”

“You know I can’t”-you mumbled as the heat from your cheeks decreased, flying out of your grasp as your breakable hope. You could not live here, even though you would love to; for your alarm clock would start screaming early in the morning to announce a new day of a normal path. Before speaking again, Namjoon tucked your hand and walked you to his father’s throne. He twirled you on your heels, a giggle emanating from your chest before he led you to his mother’s space and motioned you to sit.

Your eyes widened but Namjoon was already taking his father’s place, a royal aura embedded with the importance of the object. Feeling confident, you sat on the comfortable cushion and let yourself relax and enjoy the last bit of dream you could catch-“When you return”-Namjoon whispered, gazing at his people with a sparkle flickering inside his iris-“You will be here, with me. And although we might not visit each other endlessly, we can always make the most out of the hours we spend together…”

His head swagger to his side and you felt how tears cascaded out of your eyes, the crystal curtain blurring your view. However, you still could devise Namjoon’s dazzling grin and the delicate dimple decorating his tanned cheek and, with all the emotions stirring in your stomach, you could not neglect the offer-“Then I will try to sleep every time I can”

“I will always wait for you”-he declared.

“I will always dream about you”-you swore.

“I love you”-he stated and, as you vanished from his sight, you held his gloved hand and muttered-“I love you too, Namjoon”

Opening your eyes, heaviness fell upon you. Nevertheless, as you turned off the beeping sound of the demonic device resting beside you, your palm tickled with a phantom touch. A shiver bugged your spine and before you even knew what was happening, you were eager to go back to sleep. Eager to return to that marvellous world where you could laugh and dance and smile without restraint.

Eager to see him once again.
